Base Script for image -> video

#imagetovideo.sh
ffmpeg -i image-%03d.dpx video.ffv1

If gnu parrallel is used:

Considering N images needs to be encoded through P jobs

Split the images accross P folder (indexed by temporal order), shift all the image index values to have index zero in each folder, and then run:

parallel -transfer return {.}.ffv1 ::: dir_*/imagetovideo.sh

and then concat ffv1 videos in the final one.